-- Spanish Wind Power Reaches Record as North Suffers Weather Alert
-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 2012-04-16T11:55:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/spanish-wind-power-reaches-record-as-north-suffers-weather-alert.html
Spanish wind turbines covered a
record 60.5 percent of power demand on the mainland early today,
producing 12.8 gigawatts compared with 59.6 percent of demand
covered at the previous peak in November, according to the grid
operator  Red Electrica Corp. (REE)  SA.  Catalonia, Aragon and Navarre in the north of the country
as well as the mountains near  Madrid  are on alert for high
winds, the national weather service said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  